Wambi: contracted ARR expansion with Naples County Health System; continued expansions with UTMB and NKC Health; multiple go-lives anticipated in Q4 2025; ongoing cash discipline and cost management.

Siera.AI: expanding customer footprint with Schinner, Bunge Oils, Nemera, Phoenix Metals, and others; broadening pipeline across S2/S3 warehouse safety deployments; Parkway leads Series A and remains on the board.

TAE Technologies: raised over $150M in latest round with Google, Chevron Technology Ventures, and NEA; Google reaffirmed long-term investment; broader fusion energy momentum supports growth trajectory.
GTC: Parkway venture studio project focused on retail real estate development infrastructure; poised to reshape pre-development workflows and unlock SaaS potential; further updates forthcoming.

Entry price of $305M represents 13.8x LTM 3/31/2026E and 12.2x 2026E Adj. EBITDA.
High visibility into 2026P results driven by repeat customer orders, with pricing expected to drive ~60% of revenue growth and ~85% of EBITDA growth in 2026P.

FDI management team has multiple high potential upside opportunities, including wallet share expansion with existing customers (Trane and Vertiv), incremental 2026 pricing, and an opportunity to white-label Veris components.
Industry-leading brand (“Relay-in-a-Box”, “RIB”) known for quality, reliability, and ease of installation.
Core SAM growth of ~12%+ supported by macro trends such as aging infrastructure, “electrification of everything”, and data center expansion.
Datacenters make up ~15-20% of today’s commercial building market and are growing rapidly due to unprecedented growth in AI adoption.

FDI is the industry standard for many of its components, with customers rating the Company highly across key purchasing criteria.
FDI has a successful track record of introducing new products to the market and a substantial pipeline that will continue contributing to long-term growth.
L Squared has identified 228 high-priority M&A targets across the fragmented peripheral components and sensors market.
Significant opportunity for Serviceable Addressable Market (SAM) expansion via Core FDI SAM growth, New Product Development, and M&A.

FDI has been continuously voted one of Indiana’s Best Places to Work.
FDI sells primarily via distributors to blue-chip OEMs and end customers, with ~75% of revenue from distribution.
Product portfolio includes Relays, Power Supplies, Transformers, Current Sensors, Specialty Peripherals, Power Controls, and Emergency Lighting Relays.
L Squared’s Value Creation Plan includes enhancing the Executive Leadership Team and Board of Directors, New Product Development, Pricing strategies, M&A, and AI/Data Analysis implementation.

L Squared plans to reserve ~25% of initial equity to fund future M&A.
Veris is undergoing strategic reprioritization and plans to deprioritize production of its branded current sensors and relays, creating an opportunity for FDI to take over these product lines.
FDI recently won a new opportunity to serve a critical component for Vertiv's Power Distribution Units (PDUs), with Vertiv increasing demand outlook.
FDI secured a new data center OEM program via Trane Technologies, supplying current sensors for their Cooling Distribution Unit line.

Significant opportunity for SAM expansion into adjacent product categories (Sensors, Electromechanical Controls) and applications (Access Control, Fire & Life Safety, Vertical Transportation).
Key Risks identified include 'overstocking' by end customers, customer concentration, tariffs, and M&A execution, each with mitigating factors.
The transaction is anticipated to sign on January 30th, 2026, with capital calls in early to mid-February and closing estimated late February 2026.
L Squared has completed extensive market diligence calls via an expert network with distributors, OEMs, and end customers.
Acquisition multiples for scaled HVAC/R and peripheral components providers are consistently in the low-to-mid teens, with relevant comps trading at 15x-17x+.
L Squared has engaged with potential advisors and Board of Directors members to bring market insights and customer connections.
FDI provides energy-efficient products that help customers stay ahead of industry and regulatory trends while lowering operating costs and reducing environmental impact.
